  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nYannick requested a comprehensive market valuation for a T3 apartment in Résidence des Castalies, Annecy, for purchase negotiation. Manus conducted detailed market analysis using comparable sales data, evaluating a 7th floor unit with architectural features and division potential. The analysis established a fair market value of €333,505 with a negotiation range of €316,829-€350,180, supported by three direct comparables within the same residence. A complete valuation report was produced and optimized for negotiation use.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nUser needs professional real estate valuation for apartment purchase negotiation in senior residence, requiring defensible pricing based on concrete market data rather than speculation\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nConducted comprehensive market analysis including comparable sales research within same residence, evaluated architectural features and location premium, analyzed senior residence market dynamics, calculated fair market value with negotiation range\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [market_analysis] Real Estate Valuation Report — Complete apartment valuation with comparable sales data, pricing methodology, and negotiation strategy\n- [executive_summary] Optimized Negotiation Report — Condensed 2-page version focusing on key negotiation points and market positioning\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Established €333,505 as fair market value\n- Defined negotiation range of €316,829-€350,180\n- Identified three key comparables within same residence\n- Confirmed 38% senior residence market discount\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Direct comparables within same building provided strong valuation foundation\n- Architectural features (vaults, French doors) properly valued as premium elements\nFailed / suboptimal:\n\n- Initial report was too lengthy for practical negotiation use\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Senior residence market shows consistent 38% discount vs general market\n- Division potential adds significant value to T3 apartments\n\n## Challenges & Blockers\n\n- Need to balance comprehensive analysis with concise presentation for negotiation\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Actual asking price from seller not yet known\n- Timeline for negotiation process\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Use valuation report for purchase negotiation\n- Apply identified negotiation range based on market analysis\n- Consider division potential as additional value argument\n---\nUID: u1Y1Rj2CLx4MPR5OWsHBbg | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0149\n"
